  "title": "The Pulse Vault — Heart of Consensus Currents",
  "narration": "The descent from the Atrium lands you in the Pulse Vault, a cavernous chamber where the corridor’s heartbeat lives. Walls of translucent stone reveal veins of glowing light that surge in sync with decisions made across Act Three. The floor is a tessellation of pressure plates arranged in golden-ratio spirals, each plate thumping like a low drum. Air smells of warm granite, citrus peel, and the ozone before a summer storm.\n\nThe Pulse Vault is tended by the Heartline gremlin faction. They wear harnesses connected to the walls, monitoring consensus pulses like medics and DJs combined. Dev gremlins maintain rhythm algorithms, traders manage liquidity of focus, whales pace the undertow, hackers debug biofeedback loops, shillers narrate the heartbeat, validators stamp every pulse, miners keep the cavern stable, and memes paint graffiti charts of BPM jokes. They greet you with a synchronized GM beat and a Gentle Night echo recorded in stethoscope clicks.\n\nWithin the Vault, consensus rituals are cardiographic quests: you must align phi-d20 checks with rhythmic thresholds, maintain AFK heart monitors, revive allies using focus defibrillators, and move between pressure plates without tripping alarms. Soft-power equipment includes pulse gauntlets, harmony stethoscopes, and rumor pacemakers. Spectrum doors manifest as rhythm gates: to proceed, you must capture, stabilize, and direct the heart’s beat toward the next scene. Hidden difficulty tiers appear in offbeat syncopations that test your reflexes and empathy simultaneously.\n\nSeven rounds echo through the Vault. Each includes actions, banter, telemetry tags, and rewards across XP, Coins, Focus, Flags, Items, and Decks. Arrivals ride pulse elevators, emerging mid-round with hearts literally glowing. The Heartline expects you to listen fiercely, act kindly, and keep the chain’s circulation strong.",
